h1. TGS Flow Pilot

h2. Overview

TGS Flow enables two capabilities:

* Generate Jira compliant backlog items from planning artifacts
* Automatically reconcile GitHub engineering activity back into Jira so work in progress reflects real execution

This pilot validates the workflow end to end before expanding usage across CORE.

---

h2. Pilot Goals

The pilot will validate that teams can:

* Generate backlog items from requirements, solution docs, or meeting notes
* Assign engineering work through those backlog items
* Automatically update Jira based on GitHub activity
* Reduce manual Jira updates
* Improve visibility into real engineering work

---

h2. Pilot Scope

Two supported participation paths:

h3. Path A – TGS Flow VS Code Extension

Teams use the TGS Flow repository and VS Code extension to:

* Generate backlog items
* Reconcile GitHub commits with Jira work

h3. Path B – Claude Jira CLI

Some participants may use the Claude Jira CLI integration being piloted by R2E.

Questions related to the CLI workflow should be directed to the CLI support lead.

