h2. Pilot Timeline

h3. Sprint 1 – Onboarding and Validation

*Dates:* March 19 – April 1

*Objective*

Each participant and their team installs the tooling and validates the workflow.

*Expected Outcomes*

* Install and configure tooling
* Run an initial workflow test
* Identify the real use case that will run in Sprint 2
* Confirm which engineers must participate
* Validate the workflow works end to end

h3. Sprint 1 Test Definition

Each participant must run a small validation test to confirm the workflow works before participating in Sprint 2.

The purpose of the test is to validate:

* Tool installation
* Backlog generation
* Jira integration
* Team access setup

The test should create a minimal amount of Jira content.

h4. Required Test Scope

The test should generate only:

* 1 Epic
* 1 Story

These should be created from a simple test document or notes.

Example source artifact:

* Short solution note
* Small design outline
* Meeting notes

The goal is to validate that the workflow works, not to generate real backlog.

h4. Test Steps

# Install and configure the tool

# Generate backlog from a simple source document

# Confirm the Epic and Story are created in Jira

# Verify the tickets contain expected fields

# Confirm the participant has access to assign work

# Define the real use case that will be executed in Sprint 2

# Confirm the engineers required for the Sprint 2 use case

# Ensure those engineers complete setup if they will participate

h3. Test Data Cleanup Requirement

The Sprint 1 test should create minimal Jira content.

To avoid cluttering Jira projects:

* Only create 1 Epic and 1 Story
* Use a clearly identifiable naming pattern

Example naming convention:

{code}
[TGS TEST] Example Backlog Generation
{code}

After the test is completed:

* Participants should notify the pilot admins in Slack
* Pilot admins will remove the test artifacts

Note: Not all participants will have permission to delete Jira issues. If cleanup is required, pilot administrators will handle deletion.

The purpose of this process is to prevent Jira hygiene issues during the pilot.

---

h3. Sprint 2 – Real Use Case Execution

*Dates:* April 2 – April 15

*Objective*

Each team runs one real engineering use case through the workflow.

*Expected Outcomes*

Teams should:

* Use a real requirements artifact or solution document
* Generate backlog items
* Assign work to engineers
* Execute the work
* Validate that GitHub activity updates Jira
* Provide feedback on workflow gaps or friction

*Sprint 2 Demonstration*

At the end of the sprint each team should show:

* Source artifact used
* Generated backlog
* Jira tickets created
* Engineers assigned
* Jira updates during execution
* Feedback and improvement suggestions

